{
  "texts": [
    "However, the responsible teams will often have incentives to focus on day-to-day operations, rather than thinking about thorny ethical questions.",
    "It therefore seems desirable to have an additional \"layer of defense\", especially when dealing with catastrophic risks.",
    "The underlying concept is called \"defense in depth\" [46].",
    "But supporting risk assessments could also have negative effects.",
    "If other teams rely on the board's work, they might assess risks less thoroughly."
  ]
}